y, he said, it is less pleasant than I should have thought.\n\n- Samuel Beckett, Malone Dies\n|\nThe future toyed with us, it was up to us to try to enjoy the game. But not everyone liked the game or they weren't given the tools to play.\n\n- Carrie Adams, The Godmother\n|\nWhen you write, you write out of your best self. Everything else drops away.\n\n- Salman\n|\nThose friends thou hast, and their adoption tried,Grapple them to thy soul with hoops of steel;But do not dull thy palm with entertainmentOf each new-hatch'd, unfledg'd comrade.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Hamlet\n|\nIf I know that I can do something that makes me happy, why do I allow myself to get so depressed?\n\n- Kara Lee Corthron, The Truth of Right Now\n|\nWriting things was important, wasn't it? Nakata asked.'Yes, it was. The process of writing was important. Even though the finished product is completely meaningless.\n\n- Haruki Murakami, Kafka on the Shore\n|\nFiction that adds up, that suggests a 'logical consistency,' or an explanation of some kind, is surely second-rate fiction; for the truth of life is its mystery.\n\n- Joyce Carol Oates, The Journal of Joyce Carol Oates: 1973-1982\n|\nWe have something very valuable, for which we have not yet found an application in this life\n\n- Sunday\n|\nSometimes one really need to have a spiritual eyes and mind, to be able to see and understand somethings\n\n- Nurudeen\n|\nKnowledge was like candy: you never turned it down, especially if you didn't have to work too hard to get it.\n\n- Robert Liparulo, House of Dark Shadows\n|\nBy not stepping into your greatness, you are letting down everyone around you whom you can inspire, touch, or influence.\n\n- Amber Hurdle, The Bombshell Business Woman: How to Become a Bold, Brave, and Successful Female Entrepreneur\n|\nWe lusty bibliophiles know that reading, unlike just about anything else, is both good for you and loads of fun.\n\n- Kevin Smokler, Bookmark Now: Writing in Unreaderly Times: A Collection of All