nd you'll find ultimate success and fulfillment.\n\n- Amy\n|\nStop thinking that racism is fun until a racist person get under your skin, that's when you'll know racism is not fun.\n\n- Werley Nortreus, Best Quotes of Werley Nortreus\n|\nWhy do we complicate life, when it was meant to be very simple?\n\n- Janvier Chouteu-Chando, The Girl on the Trail\n|\nHumor is a spontaneous, wonderful bit of an outburst that just comes. It's unbridled, its unplanned, it's full of suprises.\n\n- Erma\n|\nWhat you need, is an Event, to remember for a lifetime.\n\n- Rehan\n|\nArt stands on the shoulders of craft, which means that to get to the art, you must master the craft. If you want to write, practice writing.\n\n- Ann Patchett, The Getaway Car: A Practical Memoir About Writing and Life\n|\nYou thought I was a werewolf?' Dervish asks.'Yes' I answer hollowly.'You ass.\n\n- Darren Shan, Lord Loss\n|\nI write entirely to find out what I'm thinking, what I'm looking at, what I see and what it means. What I want and what I fear.\n\n- Joan\n|\nWhen you invest your life, you are multiplying it.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nThe truth of course was otherwise, but Lecha had never felt she owed anyone the truth, unless it was truth about their own lives, and then they had to pay her to tell them.\n\n- Leslie Marmon Silko, Almanac of the Dead\n|\nI don't write stories, I write characters.\n\n- Bhavya\n|\nAs long as one is the doer of the actions, there is agnan [all other knowledge other than one’s own true self, wordly knowledge]. Agnan is the cause for the worldly life.\n\n- Dada\n|\nSome people say, ‘Do not judge the book by its cover!’ Well, I say not to judge at all. People can say anything they want to say, but for me, cover does matter.\n\n- Toba\n|\nThe truth doesn't always make a good story, does it?\n\n- Lev Grossman, The Magicians\n|\nThey don't actually want you to do your own thing, 